header.gameNote: WILLIAM amp; MARY CLASSIC AT WILLIAMSBURG VA

article.headline: High Point 70, Maine 67
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Arizona Reid had 24 points, including two late free throws, to help High Point claim third place by beating Maine 70-67 in the William & Mary Tip-Off Classic Saturday night. Reid also grabbed 12 rebounds. Justin Dunn added 12 points. High Point jumped out to a nine-point lead, but Maine brought it to within 1 with 7:40 left in the half. It took more than two minutes for either to score again, and it was Maine who took the lead off a layup by Ernest Turner. High Point regained the lead at 24-23 with 4:23 left in the half and never trailed again. The Panthers went into the break up 36-32. High Point opened the second half with an 11-0 run, with Reid contributing six, to go up 47-32 with 16:21 remaining. Maine clawed back, going on a 16-5 run, fueled by 10 from Jon Sheets, to come to within three. Issa Konare fouled Chris Bruff with 40 seconds left, and Bruff hit both shots to bring Maine to within one. Turner then fouled Reid, who sank both his shots. Freddy Petkus missed a 3-pointer at the buzzer that would have tied it. Sheets had 22, and Turner 21 for Maine, who was perfect from the charity stripe, sinking all 18 shots.
